<task id="AIPU2-035" project="Spaarke AI Platform Unification R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Build PromptLibraryService with 4-tier ownership</title>
    <phase>2C</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, cosmos-db, prompts</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>AIPU2-002, AIPU2-006</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    Build a PromptLibraryService that enables users to save, reuse, and share prompt templates
    across four ownership tiers: personal (user-owned, private), team (shared within a team),
    org (organization-wide read-only, admin-managed), and system (built-in read-only, shipped
    with the product). Personal and team templates are stored in Cosmos DB `prompts` container.
    Org and system templates are stored in Dataverse (sprk_prompttemplate table) for admin
    tooling compatibility. Templates support variable substitution with entity-reference pickers
    (e.g., {{matter.name}}, {{document.title}}). Expose full CRUD API endpoints for personal
    and team tiers; read-only endpoints for org and system tiers.
  </prompt>
  <role>Senior .NET developer familiar with Cosmos DB, Dataverse OData, and .NET Minimal API endpoint design.</role>
  <goal>
    Users can save a prompt template, retrieve it later, share it with their team, and use
    variable placeholders that resolve to live Dataverse entity values. CRUD endpoints work
    for personal and team tiers. Org and system templates are read-only via the same API.
    Template variables are documented and validated.
  </goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/constraints/data.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Read data.md constraints to confirm storage patterns for user-scoped vs org-scoped data before implementing.</step>
    <step>Create PromptLibraryService.cs in src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Prompts/. Define IPromptLibraryService with GetTemplatesAsync(userId, teamId, scope), GetTemplateByIdAsync(id, userId), CreateTemplateAsync(template, userId), UpdateTemplateAsync(id, template, userId), DeleteTemplateAsync(id, userId), and RenderTemplateAsync(template, variables) methods.</step>
    <step>Define PromptTemplate record: Id, Title, Description, Body (string with {{variable}} placeholders), Tier (enum: Personal/Team/Org/System), OwnerId (userId or teamId), Tags (list of string), Variables (list of TemplateVariable: name, description, entityType?), CreatedAt, UpdatedAt.</step>
    <step>Implement Cosmos DB CRUD for Personal and Team tiers: partition key /ownerId. Personal templates: ownerId = userId. Team templates: ownerId = teamId. Use DefaultAzureCredential.</step>
    <step>Implement Dataverse read for Org and System tiers: query sprk_prompttemplate via OData filter on sprk_tier field. Map to PromptTemplate record.</step>
    <step>Implement RenderTemplateAsync: replace {{variable.field}} placeholders with resolved values from a provided Dictionary of string to string. Return rendered string. Validate all required variables are provided; return ValidationResult listing missing variables if not.</step>
    <step>Add Minimal API endpoints in a PromptLibraryEndpoints.cs file: GET /api/ai/prompts (list by scope), GET /api/ai/prompts/{id}, POST /api/ai/prompts, PUT /api/ai/prompts/{id}, DELETE /api/ai/prompts/{id}, POST /api/ai/prompts/{id}/render. Apply DocumentAuthorizationFilter for ownership checks.</step>
    <step>Register PromptLibraryService in AddAiPersistenceModule. Map endpoints in Program.cs.</step>
    <step>Write unit tests: (a) list returns personal + team + org + system templates merged, (b) create/update/delete only allowed for personal/team, (c) org/system are read-only (delete throws Forbidden), (d) render resolves variables correctly, (e) render returns validation error for missing variables.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Four tiers are supported: Personal and Team (Cosmos CRUD), Org and System (Dataverse read-only).</criterion>
    <criterion>Template variables use {{variable.field}} syntax and are resolved by RenderTemplateAsync.</criterion>
    <criterion>Attempting to update or delete an Org or System template returns HTTP 403 Forbidden.</criterion>
    <criterion>CRUD endpoints are registered and return correct HTTP status codes (201 Created, 204 No Content, 404 Not Found).</criterion>
    <criterion>Cosmos documents partition by /ownerId (userId or teamId) — not by tenantId alone.</criterion>
    <criterion>Service registered in AddAiPersistenceModule and resolves cleanly.</criterion>
    <criterion>All unit tests pass (dotnet test).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
